        <property propertyId="38f94dd1-d5aa-41b8-b182-c0c42985d9dc" amount="0.006511332" unitId="7b75baf0-cbee-45e6-bf66-af119da06553">
          <name xml:lang="en">price</name>
          <unitName xml:lang="en">EUR2005</unitName>
          <comment xml:lang="en">Price, average unit value, dollars per metric ton in 2022 of construction sand and gravel of 11 USD/metric ton. Same price for the products "sand" and "gravel, round", since they are quarried together. The price is the annual average free-on-board plant prices, usually at the first point of sale or captive use, as reported by construction-sand-and-gravel-producing companies. This value does not include transportation from the plant or yard to the consumer. it does, however, include all costs of mining, processing, in-plant transportation, overhead, and profit. Value retrieved from USGS, Mineral Commodity Summaries 2023, accessed on 20230918: https://pubs.usgs.gov/periodicals/mcs2023/mcs2023-sand-gravel.pdf from https://www.usgs.gov/centers/national-minerals-information-center/construction-sand-and-gravel-statistics-and
The price was converted to EUR based on the annual exchange rates published by the European Central Bank (https://sdw.ecb.europa.eu/quickview.do?SERIES_KEY=120.EXR.A.USD.EUR.SP00.A, last accessed on 2023-06-01) and adjusted for inflation relative to 2005 using the producer price index (PPI) of the euro area, published by eurostat (https://ec.europa.eu/eurostat/databrowser/view/STS_INPP_A__custom_6416181/default/table?lang=en, last accessed on 2023-06-01).																	
</comment>
        </property>
